description:
Toronto Nature Stewards program - plant inventory.

Newtonbrook Ravine creek, from Finch Ave East south to Forest Grove Driive.

I took this particular photo because I feel like I don't see Blue Jays hanging onto plants like this very often. But when I looked at the photos, I also noticed that it looks as though this jay has something on his or her chest feathers, which could be blood. In the second shot it even looks like the tip of the beak might have something red stuck to it. It seems possible that shortly before striking this pose this jay had been scavenging carrion or had even killed something themselves. (Or they're just messy and the pinky colour is a trick of the light!)
